# Agent Lightning Boundaries

Agent Lightning is optional and subordinate to the core workflow.

It may optimize only these development-workflow surfaces:
- execution-agent strategy
- reviewer precision and evidence quality
- review-mode recommendation under policy constraints
- remediation prioritization and batching

It must not control:
- scope or intent authority
- in-scope versus out-of-scope decisions
- hard governance rules
- mandatory reviewer coverage in `full` mode
- local quality-gate requirements

Rules:
- treat cost and query reduction as subordinate to completing a real full QA pass
- never recommend skipping a reviewer or quality gate that policy requires
- treat `.codex/config/review-scope.yaml` as final authority for review-mode eligibility
- record when a recommendation is blocked or overridden by policy
- record which invariant or policy clause allowed or blocked each recommendation
- keep telemetry separate from canonical scope memory

Definition of a successful optimization:
- fewer LLM or agent queries to reach a full QA pass
- lower estimated LLM cost to reach a full QA pass
- no loss of reviewer coverage, finding quality, finding yield, or in-scope remediation completeness
